article.headline: Liberty 78, Radford 71
article.story: LYNCHBURG, CVa. (AP) -- Anthony Smith scored 29 points and B.J. Jenkins added 18 Saturday night, leading Liberty to a 78-71 victory against Radford. The Flames (15-15, 7-7 Big South) led 33-28 at halftime. Radford (10-19, 5-9 Big South) was led by Joey Lynch-Flohr with 19 points and Amir Johnson with 15. Eric Hall added 14, all in the second half.
